author: app.com
title: Football: Red Bank rushes past Neptune to remain undefeated
text:
MORE LITTLE SILVER On a rain-drenched evening when Red Bank honored its storied, undefeated 1975 state championship-winning team, the Bucs extended its streak to four consecutive victories in this 2015 season with a 28-7 dismissal of Class B North foe Neptune.
Red Bankâ€™s rushing attack proved too much for the Scarlet Fliers (0-4), as the Bucs (4-0) racked up 367 yards and each of its four scores on the ground, an effort led by senior tailback Alim Godsey.
After the teams traded punts on their first possessions, Godsey provided Red Bank a lead late in the first quarter, capping a seven-play drive with an 18-yard touchdown run up the middle, shedding a defender at the five, before lowering his shoulder at the one and barreling into the end zone.
